RWE Board to Approve Capital Boost on Aug. 8, Platow Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-08-05T17:54:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/rwe-board-to-approve-capital-boost-on-aug-8-platow-reports.html
RWE AG (RWE) ’s supervisory board will
approve a capital increase for the utility on Aug. 8 as it tries
to cut debt, the  Platow Brief  newsletter reported today, without
citing anyone.  Supervisory board chairman Manfred Schneider will nominate
RWE’s Essent NV’s unit Management Board Chairman Peter Terium to
become deputy chairman of Essen, Germany-based RWE under  Juergen Grossmann , Platow said, without saying where it got the
information.  RWE’s chief spokesman, Volker Heck, contacted late today by
telephone, declined to comment on Platow’s report on a capital
increase and whether Terium will be nominated.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net . 